'''Hal Dominic Bart Cruttenden''' (born 9 September 1969) is an English stand-up comedian, writer and actor<ref>{{cite news|first=Nosheen |last=Iqbal |url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2009/apr/28/comedian-hal-cruttenden |title=Comedian profile: Hal Cruttenden |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=29 April 2009 |accessdate=10 April 2015}}</ref> who has appeared on ''[[Mock the Week]], Live at the Referendum, [[Live at the Apollo (TV series)|Live At The Apollo]], [[Have I Got News for You]], [[The 11 O'Clock Show]]'', [[Richard Herring's interview podcasts|''Richard Herring's Leicester Square Podcast'']], and ''[[The Great British Bake Off: An Extra Slice]]''. 

He has also written for ''[[The Omid Djalili Show]]'' and ''[[The Rob Brydon Show]]''. He was nominated for Best Newcomer at the 2002 [[Edinburgh Comedy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chortle.co.uk/comics/h/455/hal_cruttenden |title=Hal Cruttenden, comedian |publisher=Chortle : The UK Comedy Guide |date= |accessdate=10 April 2015}}</ref>

==Biography==
Cruttenden grew up in [[Ealing]], west London<ref>{{cite news|url=http://metro.co.uk/2008/07/22/five-questions-for-hal-cruttenden-305083/ |title=Five questions for ... Hal Cruttenden |newspaper=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |date=22 July 2008 |accessdate=10 April 2015}}</ref> and he was educated at [[St Paul's School, London|St Paul's School]]<ref name=OldPaulines>[http://www.stpaulsschool.org.uk/st-pauls/the-arts/drama/old-paulines-and-drama Old Paulines and Drama]. Retrieved 21 November 2015</ref> and the [[University of York]].<ref name=nouse>[http://www.nouse.co.uk/2015/08/26/edinburgh-fringe-2015-review-hal-cruttenden/ Edinburgh Fringe 2015 Review] Retrieved 21 November 2015</ref> He is married to Dawn Coulter-Cruttenden, an artist,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.paperdawn.co.uk/ |title=Dawn Coulter-Cruttenden |access-date=11 July 2016}}</ref> with whom he has two daughters, born in 2000 and 2002.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thisisnorthdevon.co.uk/INTERVIEW-Tony-Glynn-chats-Hal-Cruttenden-ahead/story-19785360-detail/story.html |title=Tony Glynn chats to Hal Cruttenden ahead of his show Tough Luvvie at the Plough |newspaper=[[North Devon Journal]] |date=12 September 2013 |accessdate=10 April 2015}}</ref>

Having studied acting, he had bit parts on ''[[EastEnders]]'' and ''[[Kavanagh QC]]'' in the 1990s, and voiced BBC traffic reports. At 27, he did his first comedy gig.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/entertainment/celebrity-interviews/comedian-hal-cruttenden-draws-family-6336045|title=Comedian Hal draws on family life for his gags and the results are hilarious|last=Dingwall|first=John|date=2015-08-28|work=dailyrecord|access-date=2018-05-02}}</ref>

